By Ismaila Chafe  Abuja  –  President Muhammadu Buhari has felicitated with foremost industrialist, investor and philanthropist, Alhaji Aliko Dangote, on the occasion of his 63rd birthday anniversary, wishing him and his loved ones a splendid day. The president, in a congratulatory message by his spokesman, Mr Femi Adesina, in Abuja on Friday, saluted the large-heartedness of Africa’s wealthiest man, noting that ”it is one thing to be so blessed, and another to use the wealth to the glory of God and for the good of humanity”. According to him, Dangote has always stood to be counted whenever it mattered, judging by his generous contributions to the fight against Polio, Ebola disease, the current Coronavirus, and many other challenges which have faced Nigeria and the African continent. Buhari therefore prayed God to grant the ”great son of Nigeria” long life, good health and further successes in all areas of endeavour. (NAN) By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - President Muhammadu Buhari has commended Aliko Dangote Foundation (ADF) for donating N200 million to assist in combating the influx of Covid-19 into the country. Buhari made the commendation in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr Femi Adesina, in Abuja on… March 4, 2020 In "News" By idris Abdulrahman Abuja -  The Nigeria’s agricultural sector has received a major boost as the Dangote Group and the OCP Group of Morocco signed an agreement to boost fertiliser production and business in the country. The OCP Group is a global leader in phosphate and phosphate derivatives markets. The… December 5, 2016 In "Business" There is no need for a denial. Aliko Dangote and Femi Otedola are not partisan politicians; they don’t belong to any party and couldn’t have, therefore, been named members of the “APC Presidential Campaign Council.” But they could still perform more strategic roles as members of the “APC Special Advisory… January 2, 2019 In "Opinion"